Australia blinks first in an attempt to move the game along. "I think Green was feeling sorry for the crowd and wanted to give them something," Phil Tufnell says on ABC/BBC Radio. Here comes Mitchell Starc. I can't imagine he'll block too many.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Australia were 3-92 in that session - the bouncers doing the business again in this Test match as Smith, Head and Khawaja all fell to some short stuff from England's bowlers. Australia will still want a lot more runs in this next session though - England successfully chased 378 last summer against India, and chased three over scores between 279 and 299 that first Bazball summer. So still plenty to do all round in this match.
